19 May 2022 As part of Africa Month 2022 celebrations, the Government Communication and Information System (GCIS) in partnership with the Department of Arts and Culture will host a panel discussion themed “Advancing Patriotism, Social Cohesion and Citizen's Rights to Safeguard South Africa and Its Institutions”. Since the beginning of the year 2022, South Africa is experiencing a series of unsavoury incidents that relate to the destruction of public property, violent protests and burning of state institutions. All these have had a negative effect on service delivery and take away from the progress that the country has made in improving the delivery of services to the people such as the electricity supply and rail public transport system. The discussion will explore the following: We aim to: Members of the media are invited to participate and cover the panel discussion as per the following details: Date: Thursday, 19 May 2022Time: 13h00 Virtual Platform details: Zoom Please click this URL to join. https://gcis.zoom.us/j/95645107709?pwd=WEk5NTh5OGVFcDBLVjYwRUdZMVpHQT09 Passcode: 874476 Enquiries: William Baloyi Cell: 083 390 7147